line_1: She now of this or that enquires,
He views her blooming youth, her race enquires.
line_2: But Ninus most her fortitude admires,

line_1: But first the pleasure of the gods enquires.
line_2: In vain! the king obstructs her young desires,
If he has seen its gilded Spires.

line_1: Amaz'd at this, the sleeping Turk enquires,
line_2: Why He that liv'd above, in soft Attires,

line_1: Amaz'd at this, the sleeping Turk enquires,
line_2: Now roll'd in Bliss, while t'other roll'd in Fires?
